# SwigPay — Windsurf Cascade Rules
# Penn Blockchain Conference Hackathon 2026

## Priority Order (strict — do not skip ahead)
1. Working x402 payment flow — MCP server returns 402, client auto-pays
2. Squads v4 multisig created for agent + spending limit added
3. x402 payments routed through Squads spendingLimitUse
4. SQLite transaction log (endpoint, amount, txHash, agent_id, status)
5. Demo agent (agents/demo.ts) showing rejected + approved payment
6. Next.js dashboard (minimal: table + approve button is enough)

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode, ESM imports (`import`/`export` only — NO require())
- No `any` types — use `unknown` with type guards or Zod for runtime validation
- All async functions: try/catch with descriptive console.error messages
- Log x402 events: `console.log("[x402]", { tool, amount_usdc, txHash, agent })`
- Log Squads events: `console.log("[squads]", { op, multisigPda, vaultPda })`
- File size: max 200 lines — split into modules if larger
- All config via process.env validated with Zod on startup — fail fast if missing

## Solana Rules
- DEVNET ONLY: SOLANA_NETWORK=devnet always
- Import USDC address and network ID from @x402/svm — never hardcode
- `USDC_DECIMALS = 6` — 1 USDC = 1_000_000 units — never confuse
- Squads program deployed on devnet: SQDS4ep65T869zMMBKyuUq6aD6EgTu8psMjkvj52pCf
- ALWAYS simulate transactions before broadcasting
- ALWAYS await confirmTransaction before logging success
- For spending limit amounts: use BigInt for multisigAddSpendingLimit, number for spendingLimitUse
- Fund agent wallet from Circle faucet: https://faucet.circle.com (Solana Devnet, 20 USDC)

## x402 Rules
- Use @x402/mcp (createPaymentWrapper on server, createx402MCPClient on client)
- Import ExactSvmScheme from "@x402/svm/exact/server" (server-side)
- Import ExactSvmScheme from "@x402/svm" (client-side)
- Import SOLANA_DEVNET_CAIP2, USDC_DEVNET_ADDRESS from "@x402/svm" — never hardcode
- Facilitator: https://x402.org/facilitator (supports Solana devnet)
- Price string format: "$0.001" (dollar string, middleware converts to USDC)
- Private key for x402 signer: base58-encoded, decoded with @scure/base base58.decode()
- Use createKeyPairSignerFromBytes from @solana/kit to create x402-compatible signer

## Squads v4 Rules
- SDK: @sqds/multisig v2.1.4 — import as `import * as multisig from "@sqds/multisig"`
- Permissions import: `import { Permissions, Permission, Period } from "@sqds/multisig"`
- Use multisigCreateV2 (not deprecated multisigCreate)
- Spending limit: use multisigAddSpendingLimit, amount is BigInt, period is Period.Day
- spendingLimitUse: amount is number, decimals: 6 for USDC
- Vault PDA holds funds — send USDC to vaultPda, NOT multisigPda
- getSpendingLimitPda requires both multisigPda and createKey

## Commit Convention
- `feat: [1.X] description` for phase 1
- `feat: [2.X] description` for phase 2
- etc.
- Run `pnpm typecheck` before every commit — fix before committing
- NEVER commit .env — only .env.example

## Testing Gates
- Phase 1: `curl -v http://localhost:4022/mcp` with paid tool call → must show x402 error (payment required)
- Phase 2: `pnpm --filter @swigpay/agent-wallet run test:provision` → logs vaultPda on Explorer
- Phase 3: `pnpm demo` → logs full payment + Solana Explorer tx link
- Phase 4: `open http://localhost:3000` → shows agents + transaction feed

## Fallback (Squads blocked >45 min)
If @sqds/multisig throws on account creation after 45 min of debugging:
1. Switch to plain Keypair as agent wallet in packages/agent-wallet/src/squads.ts
2. Implement spend limits in spendPolicy.ts (off-chain enforcement)
3. Mark in code: // FALLBACK: squads-integration-attempt.ts has original work
4. Still qualifies for Bounty 1 (x402 works), partially for Bounty 3 (explain fallback in README)

## Security
- NEVER hardcode private keys — always process.env
- Agent wallet: max 5 USDC on devnet (enough for demo)
- Simulate transaction before broadcast — catch failures early
- USDC amounts in logs: always show human-readable `${amount/1e6} USDC`
